Sentencas: An improved SOFC anode with excellent stability against carbon deposition with syngas as fuel is reported.
Titulo: Coking resistant Ni-La0.8Sr0.2FeO3 composite anode improves the stability of syngas-fueled SOFC

Sentencas: The anode material is Ni-La0.8Sr0.2FeO3 (LSF) composite synthesized by anhydrous impregnation.
Titulo: Coking resistant Ni-La0.8Sr0.2FeO3 composite anode improves the stability of syngas-fueled SOFC

Sentencas: After reduction in wet H-2 (3% H2O), the material partially decomposes to SrLaFeO4 and exsolved Fe.
Titulo: Coking resistant Ni-La0.8Sr0.2FeO3 composite anode improves the stability of syngas-fueled SOFC

Sentencas: The exsolved Fe forms Ni-Fe alloy with impregnated Ni.
Titulo: Coking resistant Ni-La0.8Sr0.2FeO3 composite anode improves the stability of syngas-fueled SOFC

Sentencas: The particle size of NieFe alloy is about 20-50 nm.
Titulo: Coking resistant Ni-La0.8Sr0.2FeO3 composite anode improves the stability of syngas-fueled SOFC

Sentencas: The Ni-Fe alloy nanoparticles disperse on the surface of the La0.8Sr0.2FeO3 and SrLaFeO4 oxides.
Titulo: Coking resistant Ni-La0.8Sr0.2FeO3 composite anode improves the stability of syngas-fueled SOFC

Sentencas: The increase of Ni content promotes the exsolution of Fe and increases the reaction sites of Ni-Fe alloy.
Titulo: Coking resistant Ni-La0.8Sr0.2FeO3 composite anode improves the stability of syngas-fueled SOFC

Sentencas: With the increase of the Ni content, the electrical conductivity and catalytic activity are enhanced, which improves the electrochemical performance of the single cell.
Titulo: Coking resistant Ni-La0.8Sr0.2FeO3 composite anode improves the stability of syngas-fueled SOFC

Sentencas: The cell with 10 mol.% Ni impregnated Ni-LSF as anode achieves a maximum power density of 550 mW cm(-2) at 700 degrees C fueled with syngas.
Titulo: Coking resistant Ni-La0.8Sr0.2FeO3 composite anode improves the stability of syngas-fueled SOFC

Sentencas: The strong interaction of the nano-sized Ni-Fe alloy with the LaxSryFeOz (La0.8Sr0.2FeO3 or SrLaFeO4) oxide substrate efficiently suppresses carbon deposition with high graphitization degree.
Titulo: Coking resistant Ni-La0.8Sr0.2FeO3 composite anode improves the stability of syngas-fueled SOFC

Sentencas: Besides, the SrLaFeO4 phase which can accommodate interstitial oxygen facilitates the removal of the deposited carbon.
Titulo: Coking resistant Ni-La0.8Sr0.2FeO3 composite anode improves the stability of syngas-fueled SOFC
